Four people have been arrested over the killing of a police officer inside a bus that was carjacked last week. Martin Korir, a DCI officer based at Ruaraka police station, was shot dead in the incident on Thika road last Friday night. Korir had been on his way home when a gang attacked the Neo Kenya vehicle and searched the passengers. He was robbed of his Jericho pistol, serial No. 44338518, that had 10 bullets. The four suspects include the crew of the bus. Police are looking for more suspects. Read: Cop shot dead after thugs carjack Neo Kenya bus on Thika Road Click here for the latest political news